GAME SIMULATION ENGINE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Stats-first scoring: TDs/FGs generated from team ratings; player stats
  derived to always match the scoreboard
- Realistic schedule generation: division-based scheduling with 3-year
  rotation. Per team: 6 divisional games (home+away vs each division rival),
  8 intra-conference non-divisional games (2 division draws, rotating cycle),
  4 inter-conference games. 18 games total, 288 league-wide.
  Week assignment prevents teams from playing twice in the same week.
- Morale modifier: effective OVR = rating × (1 + (morale − 75) × 0.001)
- Coaching modifier (applied in getTeamRatings):
  OC offense_rating: offenseRating += (oc_rating − 70) × 0.15
  DC defense_rating: defenseRating += (dc_rating − 70) × 0.15
  HC overall_rating: both sides += (hc_rating − 70) × 0.05
- Scheme modifier: each team's offense/defense rating adjusted based on
  roster fit to scheme (West Coast, Air Raid, Power Run, Spread, Run & Gun,
  4-3, 3-4, Zone Cover 2, Man Press, Blitz Heavy)
- Game script: trailing teams pass more; leading teams run more
- Overtime: TD wins outright; FG gives opponent a chance; no ties
- Weather: clear / rain / snow / wind with pass, rush, score multipliers
- Home field advantage: +0.5 scoring drives home; away QB accuracy penalty
- Depth chart integration: healthy players by position group; cascades to
  backups; targets distributed proportionally
- Background simulation: simulateGame runs in a worker thread (simWorker)

SEASON ADVANCE (advanceSeason in SeasonService.ts)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Order of operations per season advance:
  1. Age all non-retired players
  2. Progression / regression by dev trait + age bracket
  3. Breakout bonuses for standout season performers (age ≤ 28)
  4. Practice squad development (age ≤ 23 players, up to +3 OVR)
  5. Dev trait evolution (upgrades/downgrades based on age + OVR)
  6. Retirement (age/OVR thresholds, chance-based)
  7. Morale update based on team win%, contract year, playing time
  8. Open free agency (CPU GM cuts + resign attempts + contract expiry)
  9. Contract demand news events for elite players in final year
  10. Injury + waiver cleanup
  11. Archive season stats to career_stats_history (with team_id)
  12. Prune raw stats table (DELETE WHERE season < current − 1)
  13. Prune news events (DELETE WHERE season < next − 2; keeps 3 seasons)
  14. HOF inductions for newly retired players
  15. Season award news events (MVP, DPOY)
  16. Advance season counter

